description:
Location: secretx-pkcs11/src/lib.rs:271-284.

Current code:
    for attr in attrs {
        if let Attribute::KeyType(kt) = attr {
            if kt == KeyType::EC {
                return Pkcs11Backend::detect_ec_algorithm(&session, handle);
            } else if kt == KeyType::RSA {
                return Ok(SigningAlgorithm::RsaPss2048Sha256);
            } else {
                return Err(SecretError::Backend { ... });
            }
        }
    }

clippy::needless_else flags the chain because each branch returns. Cleaner:
    if kt == KeyType::EC {
        return Pkcs11Backend::detect_ec_algorithm(&session, handle);
    }
    if kt == KeyType::RSA {
        return Ok(SigningAlgorithm::RsaPss2048Sha256);
    }
    return Err(SecretError::Backend { ... });

Or, much better, a match (KeyType is an enum, so this is the natural form):
    return match kt {
        KeyType::EC => Pkcs11Backend::detect_ec_algorithm(&session, handle),
        KeyType::RSA => Ok(SigningAlgorithm::RsaPss2048Sha256),
        _ => Err(SecretError::Backend { ... }),
    };

The match form is idiomatic Rust for enum dispatch; the if-else-if chain reads as if KeyType is opaque.

When Ed25519 / P-384 support is added (findings .9, .10), the match form will be the natural place to extend.
